videos.description: Trae Young drains a 3-pointer from the wing to start 2-2 from the field against Kansas State.
videos.headline: Young connects from deep

videos.description: Trae Young continues his hot start by connecting for his fourth straight shot to begin the game.
videos.headline: Young continues hot start

videos.description: Trae Young puts the ball on a string for a great alley-oop to Brady Manek for the easy basket.
videos.headline: Young with perfect lob

videos.description: Dean Wade comes up with the big block on Oklahoma's Christian James, and Barry Brown takes it down court and draws the and-1.
videos.headline: Kansas State turns defense into offense

videos.description: Trae Young nails the 3-pointer with a defender's hand in his face just before time expires in the first half against Kansas State.
videos.headline: Young drains a 3 before half

videos.description: Trae Young sinks the three from the wing en route to connecting on his fifth 3-pointer of the game.
videos.headline: Young continues to find success behind the arc

videos.description: Trae Young finding the net from deep 60% of the time, knocks down his sixth 3-pointer of the game.
videos.headline: Young stays hot from 3

videos.description: Trae Young gets candid about his recent struggles and how he was able to bounce back against Kansas State, scoring 28 points and snapping the Sooners' six-game losing streak.
videos.headline: Young: 'This is a time I had to mature'
